				<td colspan="2"><span>Oh yeah.  SRo adventures have been driving me crazy <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-12.gif" border="0" alt="Mad" hspace="2" />  Been trying to open it up completely with a guildmate (he 2-boxes a shaman and monk)  and I end up with the pulling job. Seems like around 10% of the rooms have mobs I can target by clicking on them; other than that, I've got really adept at F8 directional targetting, and using the little trick someone here mentioned of &quot;/targ a&quot; (I love that targetting trick, thankyou thankyou thankyou!)
<br />
What really bugs me, is having a mob IN FRONT of me, hitting me, and I still cannot click on it with my mouse.  It's so infuriating.  I kid you not, my cat, who normally sits next to me while I play EQ, can recognise Guk adventures now, and he will get up and walk away within a few minutes of me zoning into one.  I think it's the steady stream of cursing after trying to target the nth mob with a mouse that he doesn't like. 
<br />
Tools like the SS helm are great, but when you're 3 person grouping guk, and you get one of the 'o so common' large zones, there's just no time to be summoning an eye constantly.  I usually end up bringing 3 or 4 and just locking them down while the monk kills them.  I find it less frustrating to run up to each mob, hit F8 for new target, wait for mez song to finish on previous target, and then start it on new one, than to stuff around trying to target and then lull mobs.</span></td>
